<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><Highlight kind="comment">/// All of these cast traits are meant to be implementations for useful casts</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that users may want to use that are outside the standard behavior. An</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><Highlight kind="comment">/// example of how to use a special cast called &#96;CastTrait&#96; is:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><Highlight kind="comment">/// template&lt;&gt; struct CastInfo&lt;foo, bar&gt; : public CastTrait&lt;foo, bar&gt; &#123;&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Essentially, if your use case falls directly into one of the use cases</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><Highlight kind="comment">/// supported by a given cast trait, simply inherit your special CastInfo</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><Highlight kind="comment">/// directly from one of these to avoid having to reimplement the boilerplate</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#96;isPossible/castFailed/doCast/doCastIfPossible&#96;. A cast trait can also</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><Highlight kind="comment">/// provide a subset of those functions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This cast trait just provides castFailed for the specified &#96;To&#96; type to make</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><Highlight kind="comment">/// CastInfo specializations more declarative. In order to use this, the target</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><Highlight kind="comment">/// result type must be &#96;To&#96; and &#96;To&#96; must be constructible from &#96;nullptr&#96;.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/nullablevaluecastfailed"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> To&gt; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/nullablevaluecastfailed">NullableValueCastFailed</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/nullablevaluecastfailed/#a395343c9b06cb157bfe2ccc8b39d4572"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> To <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/nullablevaluecastfailed/#a395343c9b06cb157bfe2ccc8b39d4572">castFailed</a>() &#123; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> To(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">nullptr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">); &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This cast trait just provides the default implementation of doCastIfPossible</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to make CastInfo specializations more declarative. The &#96;Derived&#96; template</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"><Highlight kind="comment">/// parameter &#42;must&#42; be provided for forwarding castFailed and doCast.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Provides a cast trait that uses a defined pointer to pointer cast as a base</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><Highlight kind="comment">/// for reference-to-reference casts. Note that it does not provide castFailed</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><Highlight kind="comment">/// and doCastIfPossible because a pointer-to-pointer cast would likely just</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><Highlight kind="comment">/// return &#96;nullptr&#96; which could cause nullptr dereference. You can use it like</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><Highlight kind="comment">/// this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><Highlight kind="comment">///   template &lt;&gt; struct CastInfo&lt;foo, bar &#42;&gt; &#123; ... verbose implementation... &#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><Highlight kind="comment">///   template &lt;&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><Highlight kind="comment">///   struct CastInfo&lt;foo, bar&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><Highlight kind="comment">///       : public ForwardToPointerCast&lt;foo, bar, CastInfo&lt;foo, bar &#42;&gt;&gt; &#123;&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> To, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> From, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ForwardTo&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This struct provides a method for customizing the way a cast is performed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It inherits from CastIsPossible, to support the case of declaring many</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="439"><Highlight kind="comment">/// CastIsPossible specializations without having to specialize the full</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="440"><Highlight kind="comment">/// CastInfo.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="441"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><Highlight kind="comment">/// In order to specialize different behaviors, specify different functions in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><Highlight kind="comment">/// your CastInfo specialization.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For isa&lt;&gt; customization, provide:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="446"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#96;static bool isPossible(const From &amp;f)&#96;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="447"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00448" /><CodeLine lineNumber="448"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For cast&lt;&gt; customization, provide:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="449"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00450" /><CodeLine lineNumber="450"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#96;static To doCast(const From &amp;f)&#96;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00451" /><CodeLine lineNumber="451"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00452" /><CodeLine lineNumber="452"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For dyn&#95;cast&lt;&gt; and the &#42;&#95;if&#95;present&lt;&gt; variants&#39; customization, provide:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00453" /><CodeLine lineNumber="453"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00454" /><CodeLine lineNumber="454"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#96;static To castFailed()&#96; and &#96;static To doCastIfPossible(const From &amp;f)&#96;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00455" /><CodeLine lineNumber="455"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00456" /><CodeLine lineNumber="456"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Your specialization might look something like this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00457" /><CodeLine lineNumber="457"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00458" /><CodeLine lineNumber="458"><Highlight kind="comment">///  template&lt;&gt; struct CastInfo&lt;foo, bar&gt; : public CastIsPossible&lt;foo, bar&gt; &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00459" /><CodeLine lineNumber="459"><Highlight kind="comment">///    static inline foo doCast(const bar &amp;b) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00460" /><CodeLine lineNumber="460"><Highlight kind="comment">///      return foo(const&#95;cast&lt;bar &amp;&gt;(b));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00461" /><CodeLine lineNumber="461"><Highlight kind="comment">///    &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00462" /><CodeLine lineNumber="462"><Highlight kind="comment">///    static inline foo castFailed() &#123; return foo(); &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00463" /><CodeLine lineNumber="463"><Highlight kind="comment">///    static inline foo doCastIfPossible(const bar &amp;b) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><Highlight kind="comment">///      if (!CastInfo&lt;foo, bar&gt;::isPossible(b))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><Highlight kind="comment">///        return castFailed();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466"><Highlight kind="comment">///      return doCast(b);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00467" /><CodeLine lineNumber="467"><Highlight kind="comment">///    &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00468" /><CodeLine lineNumber="468"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#125;;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00469" /><CodeLine lineNumber="469"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00470" /><CodeLine lineNumber="470"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The default implementations of CastInfo don&#39;t use cast traits for now because</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00471" /><CodeLine lineNumber="471"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// we need to specify types all over the place due to the current expected</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00472" /><CodeLine lineNumber="472"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// casting behavior and the way cast&#95;retty works. New use cases can and should</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00473" /><CodeLine lineNumber="473"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// take advantage of the cast traits whenever possible!</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00475" /><CodeLine lineNumber="475"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> To, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> From, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Enable = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
